              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "14Be reaction products were deflected by a",
                "large-gap dipole magnet set to a magnetic rigidity of",
                "3.55 Tm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DRFTC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two cathode readout drift chambers with",
                "dimensions of 30cm x 30 cm separated by 1.88 m was",
                "used to determine position and angle of charged",
                "particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Energy loss and total energy of charged",
                "particles were measured in 5 mm and 150 mm thick",
                "plastic  scintillators, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincident neutrons were measured with the",
                "Modular Neutron Array. The 144 plastic scintillator",
                "detectors of the array were arranged into 18 walls",
                "each 80 cm tall. The walls were assembled into two",
                "close-packed blocks located at 0deg and 23deg from",
                "the secondary beam direction, with their respective",
                "distances from the target being 650 cm and 470 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 120 MeV/u 18-O primary beam from the Coupled",
                "Cyclotron Facility bombarded a 3196 mg/cm2",
                "9Be production target. The A1900 fragment separator",
                "in conjunction with a 1050 mg/cm2 aluminum achromatic",
                "wedge degrader was used to separate and select for",
                "the 14Be secondary beam. The final energy of the beam",
                "was 59 MeV/u with a momentum spread of 2%, an",
                "intensity of approximately 1000 pps, and a purity of",
                "96.5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The energy and momentum vector of the fragments were",
                "reconstructed from a transformation matrix based on",
                "the magnetic field map."
              ]
            }
          ],
